Eniola Akinkuotu, Abuja Special Adviser to the President on Political Matters, Senator Babafemi Ojudu, has warned those stealing public funds that they will also be jailed. Ojudu said this in a Facebook post while reacting to the conviction of former Governor Orji Uzor Kalu of Abia State, who was sentenced to 12 years in prison by a Federal High Court in Ikoyi, Lagos, on Thursday. He said, “Those of you stealing now will have your day too. It shall not be long. Breaking: N7.65bn Fraud: Orji Uzor Kalu, APC Senator to spend 12 years in jail.”